20at%20a%20mere%203%25%20of%20GDP%E2%80%94far%20below%20what%E2%80%99s%20needed.%20Without%20adequate%20investment%20in%20tools%20that%20empower%20local%20governments%2C%20verify%20ground-level%20data%2C%20and%20engage%20directly%20with%20citizens%2C%20even%20the%20most%20well-intentioned%20strategies%20will%20fail%20to%20reach%20those%20who%20need%20them%20most.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20of%20the%20summit%E2%80%99s%20Q%26amp%3BA%20sessions%2C%20I%20strongly%20advocated%20for%20bottom-up%2C%20empathy-driven%20climate%20finance%20mechanisms%20%E2%80%94%20the%20kind%20that%20support%20city%20officials%20and%20frontline%20workers%2C%20not%20just%20elite%20consultants%20or%20think%20tanks.%20Because%20let%E2%80%99s%20be%20honest%3A%20the%20air%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20wait%20for%20policy%20cycles.%20And%20no%20city%20can%20be%20considered%20sustainable%20if%20its%20most%20vulnerable%20residents%20can%E2%80%99t%20breathe%20freely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COur%20cities%2C%E2%80%9D%20I%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9Care%20marked%20not%20only%20by%20pollution%20but%20by%20deep%20environmental%20injustice.%E2%80%9D%20Whether%20it%E2%80%99s%20exposure%20to%20toxic%20air%20or%20extreme%20heat%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20always%20those%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20social%20and%20economic%20pyramid%20who%20suffer%20the%20most%2C%20while%20those%20contributing%20most%20to%20the%20problem%20are%20often%20the%20best%20shielded%20from%20its%20consequences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDrawing%20from%20my%20scientific%20research%2C%20I%20pointed%20out%20that%20cars%20equipped%20with%20air%20conditioning%20and%20cabin%20air%20recirculation%20can%20significantly%20reduce%20in-cabin%20exposure%20to%20harmful%20particulate%20matter.%20But%20access%20to%20such%20protection%20in%20India%20is%20deeply%20unequal.%20A%20privileged%20few%20commute%20in%20air-conditioned%20SUVs%20with%20sealed%20cabins%2C%20while%20millions%20rely%20on%20open%20or%20poorly%20ventilated%20buses%2C%20rickshaws%2C%20or%20walk%20long%20distances%20in%20polluted%20air.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20injustice%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20end%20there.%20The%20poorest%20residents%2C%20often%20living%20on%20the%20peripheries%20of%20cities%20where%20pollution%20levels%20are%20highest%2C%20have%20the%20fewest%20resources%20to%20cope.%20Contrast%20this%20with%20affluent%20neighbourhoods%E2%80%94from%20South%20Delhi%20to%20South%20Gurgaon%E2%80%94where%20lower%20traffic%20density%2C%20better%20infrastructure%2C%20and%20greater%20green%20cover%20provide%20a%20protective%20microenvironment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20within%20homes%2C%20the%20gap%20widens.%20The%20wealthy%20can%20afford%20indoor%20air%20purifiers%20and%20high-end%20cooling%20systems.%20The%20middle%20class%20is%20still%20struggling%20to%20afford%20basic%20air%20conditioning.%20And%20the%20poor%3F%20They%E2%80%99re%20completely%20left%20out%20of%20this%20private%20adaptation.%20This%20isn%E2%80%99t%20just%20an%20infrastructure%20gap%20%E2%80%94%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20justice%20gap.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%E2%80%99s%20why%20I%20continue%20to%20push%20for%20empathetic%2C%20grounded%20climate%20action%20%E2%80%94%20where%20data%20informs%20decisions%2C%20but%20lived%20experience%20drives%20urgency.%20Empowering%20those%20at%20the%20frontlines%2C%20not%20overlooking%20them%2C%20must%20be%20our%20priority.%20Because%20a%20city%20where%20only%20the%20privileged%20can%20breathe%20safely%20is%20not%20a%20sustainable%20city.%20And%20until%20the%20weakest%20among%20us%20can%20live%20with%20dignity%2C%20none%20of%20us%20can%20truly%20claim%20to%20be%20resilient.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F05%2Ffeatured-img-1_11zon-1747833653.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22At%20HBS%202047%2C%20Dr%20Ashish%20Sharma%20met%20Prof%20Tarun%20Khanna%20to%20discuss%20inclusive%2C